          the height above the ground at time <m>t</m> of a falling object is given by <m>s(t) = -4.9t^{2} + v_{\mbox{<m>0</m>} }t + s_{\mbox{<m>0</m>} }</m> where <m>s</m> is in meters,
          <m>t</m> is in seconds,
          <m>v_{\mbox{<m>0</m>} }</m> is the object's initial velocity in meters per second and <m>s_{\mbox{<m>0</m>} }</m> is its initial position in meters.
